<ul>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-2892</a> (&quot;The Flying Dutchman &quot;) - Tharr she blows you up. Written by CooCooCachoo.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-2573</a> (&quot;I ain’t never heard of no commy Fifthists or nothin'.&quot;) - <em>You know, it's like I always say, when a shoggoth—excuse me, a tsürga-ouláth, the PC police will be after me if I throw words like &quot;shoggoth&quot; around—lays around the house, it really lays AROUND the HOUSE.</em> Published by ch00bakka.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-2743</a> (&quot;Nadia&quot;) - Dance for me, ballerina. Dance so that the world can fear you. Choreographed by Moenennbys.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc22"><span>Tales:</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">Directive Legends</a> - The greatest mistakes are sometimes made by those who are supposed to prevent them. Written by DrMagnus.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">Backstage</a> - There is a conspiracy afoot behind the stage on which the Foundation performs. Continued in <a class="newpage" href="#">*Unexpected Visitors and Warm Welcomes</a>. Written by Esheter.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc23"><span>Hubs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a class="newpage" href="#">Jefferson Submarine</a> - <em>A story of war, inner demons, outer demons, romance, and the end of the world in Three Acts</em>. Written by Agent MacLeod.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h4 id="toc24"><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>A Random Day diligently scoured the web for all manner of fan art, but if he missed anything, let him or rumetzen know!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc25"><span>Fanart</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=11682556">Иagi</a> produces some nicely stylish posters for articles on the Japanese wiki!</li>
<li>Check out <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=62488116">SCP-2223-6 relaxing during the end of the world</a> and <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=62468489">a member of the Unclean on the hunt</a> by <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=3316434">おもちゃ好き屋さん</a>.</li>
<li>This <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-743">chocolate fountain</a> is not one that <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=62200512">this Scout should be tasting</a>&#8230; drawn by <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=4599056">ウェルト</a>.</li>
<li>If SCP-076 is smiling at you, <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=62211972">then you'd better start running.</a> Drawn by <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=1915872">陣内</a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="http://scp-foundation.deviantart.com/">Official SCP DeviantArt hub</a> has been revived under the oversight of subtletea!</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>Thanks for tuning in again, folks! If you're unsatisfied with the blurb(s) provided for the article(s) you wrote, feel free to change it. Of course, you could just avoid that problem entirely by sending A Random Day or rumetzen a blurb for your article. We may or may not use it (if we can think of something more attention-getting, though we can try to stick with one you give us) but we'd really would just like them in order to make the process easier for making these. This is a community thing, and we want authors to give their blurbs to sell these articles much easier. It reduces the workload we have to do, and helps the news come out that much earlier!</p>
<p>Thank you all for continuing to be an excellent community &lt;3</p>
